---
import DemoComponentCard from '../../../../components/DemoComponentCard.astro';
---

<p class='text-body-large'>The component supports the same field states as other Peacock inputs, and it also validates URL format automatically when editing ends.</p>

<DemoComponentCard lang={'html'}>
  <wc-url-field
    label='Disabled URL'
    value='https://example.com/disabled'
    disabled
  ></wc-url-field>
</DemoComponentCard>

<DemoComponentCard lang={'html'}>
  <wc-url-field
    label='Read only URL'
    value='https://example.com/read-only'
    readonly
  ></wc-url-field>
</DemoComponentCard>

<DemoComponentCard lang={'html'}>
  <wc-url-field
    label='Warning state'
    value='https://example.com/legacy'
    warning
    warning-text='This endpoint is still available, but a new URL is preferred.'
  ></wc-url-field>
</DemoComponentCard>

<DemoComponentCard lang={'html'}>
  <wc-url-field
    label='Forced error state'
    value='https://example.com/error'
    error
    error-text='This URL is already in use by another record.'
  ></wc-url-field>
</DemoComponentCard>

<p class='text-body-large'>For built-in validation, enter an invalid URL while editing and blur the field. The component emits <code>input-invalid</code> and shows <code>Please enter a valid URL</code>.</p>